3. Application Load Balancer
SECTION 1: Launch Two EC2 Instances (Web Servers) in the Same VPC + AZ for Demo

1. Login to AWS Console
2. Go to EC2 > Instances > Launch Instances

Instance 1:
3. Name: `cst-R9ST-WebServer1-Red9SysTech`
4. Amazon Machine Image: Amazon Linux 2023 AMI (Free tier eligible)
5. Instance type: t2.micro (Free tier eligible)
6. Key pair: Create new or use existing one (name it `cst-R9ST-Key-Red9SysTech`)
7. Network settings:
- Allow HTTPS, HTTP, and SSH from Anywhere (0.0.0.0/0)
8. Configure storage: Default (8 GiB gp2)
9. Launch instance

Instance 2:
10. Repeat steps 2-9
11. Name: `cst-R9ST-WebServer2-Red9SysTech`

Configure Both EC2 Web Servers with Sample App
12. Once both instances are in “Running” state, select each instance > Connect > SSH Client
13. Copy the SSH command and connect to both instances in separate terminals

Run below commands in both instances:
…
#!/bin/bash
echo "Red9SysTech: Starting Bootstrap Script for Apache Web Server"
yum update -y
yum install -y httpd
systemctl start httpd
systemctl enable httpd
echo "<h1>Red9SysTech - EC2 Web Server 1 Deployed Successfully via Bootstrap</h1>" >
/var/www/html/index.html # For Server1
